<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1563,1908]" box="[151,289,1563,1588]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis box="[151,289,1563,1588]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1563,1908]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Specimens small, largest 
<quantity box="[486,569,1602,1628]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="60.0">60 mm</quantity>
long. Colour in life olive green to brown with black papillae arising from yellowish green warts, 
<specimenCount box="[423,583,1642,1668]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
with bright yellow patch on ventral surface near anus. Cuvierian tubules present. Table discs 
<quantity box="[395,518,1682,1708]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="55.0" valueMax="80.0" valueMin="30.0">30–80 µm</quantity>
and with eight marginal holes (
<figureCitation box="[902,1045,1682,1708]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="27.[151,255,1188,1212]" captionTargetBox="[201,1404,189,1141]" captionTargetId="figure-254@27.[168,1419,173,1162]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 12. Holothuria (Platyperona) difficilis Semper. SAM–A27934. Durban. A. Tables from dorsal body wall; B. buttons from dorsal body wall; C. buttons from ventral body wall; D. papillae rod and plate; E. tubefeet plates; F. madreporite; G. part of calcareous ring. (A.–C. scale a; D. scale b)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5077037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5077037/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figure 12A</figureCitation>
); spire height 
<quantity box="[1218,1344,1682,1708]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.65" metricValueMax="8.5" metricValueMin="4.8" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="66.5" valueMax="85.0" valueMin="48.0">48–85 µm</quantity>
. Dorsal buttons (
<figureCitation box="[252,388,1722,1748]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="27.[151,255,1188,1212]" captionTargetBox="[201,1404,189,1141]" captionTargetId="figure-254@27.[168,1419,173,1162]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 12. Holothuria (Platyperona) difficilis Semper. SAM–A27934. Durban. A. Tables from dorsal body wall; B. buttons from dorsal body wall; C. buttons from ventral body wall; D. papillae rod and plate; E. tubefeet plates; F. madreporite; G. part of calcareous ring. (A.–C. scale a; D. scale b)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5077037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5077037/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figure 12B</figureCitation>
) with 3–4 pairs of holes; ventral buttons (
<figureCitation box="[877,1013,1722,1748]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="27.[151,255,1188,1212]" captionTargetBox="[201,1404,189,1141]" captionTargetId="figure-254@27.[168,1419,173,1162]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 12. Holothuria (Platyperona) difficilis Semper. SAM–A27934. Durban. A. Tables from dorsal body wall; B. buttons from dorsal body wall; C. buttons from ventral body wall; D. papillae rod and plate; E. tubefeet plates; F. madreporite; G. part of calcareous ring. (A.–C. scale a; D. scale b)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5077037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5077037/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figure 12C</figureCitation>
) larger, with 6–7 pairs of holes, and occasionally an incomplete third series outside main series, buttons 
<quantity box="[958,1098,1762,1788]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="110.0" valueMax="140.0" valueMin="80.0">80–140 µm</quantity>
. Rods and fenestrated plates of papillae (
<figureCitation box="[297,437,1802,1828]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="27.[151,255,1188,1212]" captionTargetBox="[201,1404,189,1141]" captionTargetId="figure-254@27.[168,1419,173,1162]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 12. Holothuria (Platyperona) difficilis Semper. SAM–A27934. Durban. A. Tables from dorsal body wall; B. buttons from dorsal body wall; C. buttons from ventral body wall; D. papillae rod and plate; E. tubefeet plates; F. madreporite; G. part of calcareous ring. (A.–C. scale a; D. scale b)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5077037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5077037/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figure 12D</figureCitation>
) with uneven margins. Tubefeet with rods and plates (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1242,1802,1828]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="27.[151,255,1188,1212]" captionTargetBox="[201,1404,189,1141]" captionTargetId="figure-254@27.[168,1419,173,1162]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 12. Holothuria (Platyperona) difficilis Semper. SAM–A27934. Durban. A. Tables from dorsal body wall; B. buttons from dorsal body wall; C. buttons from ventral body wall; D. papillae rod and plate; E. tubefeet plates; F. madreporite; G. part of calcareous ring. (A.–C. scale a; D. scale b)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5077037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5077037/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figure 12E</figureCitation>
), the latter with somewhat serrate margins and numerous small holes in 2–4 series. All podial spicules also with characteristic median optical discontinuity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,964,1963,2028]" lastBlockId="27.[151,1250,1378,1444]" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="28" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis box="[151,362,1963,1988]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Local distribution</emphasis>
<materialsCitation collectionCode="KZN" country="Mozambique" elevation="3" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="28" location="Mozambique" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" specimenCount="1">
Known only from around Durban, 
<collectionCode box="[596,656,2002,2028]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">KZN</collectionCode>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[713,870,2002,2028]" name="Mozambique" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
, 
<quantity box="[882,959,2002,2028]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="m" value="3.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="0.0">
<elevation box="[882,959,2002,2028]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="m" value="3.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="0.0">0–6 m</elevation>
</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,391,1378,1403]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">General distribution</emphasis>
Throughout tropical Indo-Pacific but not reported from the Arabian and Indian Peninsulas
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
