) originally included in 
<taxonomicName box="[413,557,1690,1715]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Holothuriidae" genus="Holothuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aspidochirotida" pageId="27" pageNumber="27" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Platyperona">
<emphasis box="[413,557,1690,1715]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Platyperona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rowe, F. W. E." box="[603,760,1690,1716]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="119 - 170" refId="ref30718" refString="Rowe, F. W. E. (1969) A review of the family Holothuriidae (Holothuroidea: Aspidochirotida). Bulletin of the British Museum of natural History (Zoology) 18 (4), 119 - 170." type="journal article" year="1969">Rowe (1969)</bibRefCitation>
, are well keyed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Deichmann, E." box="[991,1213,1690,1716]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="239 - 349" refId="ref29374" refString="Deichmann, E. (1958) The Holothuroidea collected by the ' Velero III' and ' IV' during the years 1932 - 1954, part II, Aspidochirota. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 11 (2), 239 - 349, pls 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="1958">Deichmann (1958)</bibRefCitation>
who also provides information regarding the colouration, presence or absence of Cuvierian tubules and the synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Semper. SAM" authorityYear="1868" class="Holothuroidea" family="Holothuriidae" genus="Holothuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aspidochirotida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="difficilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">H. difficilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, she does not mention the occurrence of any green forms of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Semper. SAM" authorityYear="1868" box="[1039,1171,1770,1795]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Holothuriidae" genus="Holothuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aspidochirotida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="difficilis">
<emphasis box="[1039,1171,1770,1795]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">H. difficilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but this colouration is recorded for the consubgeneric 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selenka" authorityYear="1867" box="[524,651,1810,1835]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Holothuriidae" genus="Holothuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aspidochirotida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="parvula">
<emphasis box="[524,651,1810,1835]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">H. parvula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the West Atlantic region. Since then 
<taxonomicName authority="Pawson &amp; Gust, 1981" authorityName="Pawson &amp; Gust" authorityYear="1981" class="Holothuroidea" family="Holothuriidae" genus="Holothuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aspidochirotida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="rowei" subGenus="Platyperona">
<emphasis box="[1156,1307,1810,1835]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">H. (P.) rowei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pawson, D. L. &amp; Gust, C. A." pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="873 - 877" refId="ref30562" refString="Pawson, D. L. &amp; Gust, C. A. (1981) Holothuria (Platyperona) rowei, a new sea cucumber from Florida (Echinodermata: Holothuroidea). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 94 (3), 873 - 877." type="journal article" year="1981">Pawson &amp; Gust, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Cherbonnier, 1988" authorityName="Cherbonnier" authorityYear="1988" box="[295,721,1850,1876]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Holothuriidae" genus="Holothuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aspidochirotida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="crossnieri" subGenus="Platyperona">
<emphasis box="[295,495,1850,1875]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">H. (P.) crossnieri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cherbonnier, G." box="[502,721,1850,1876]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refId="ref28924" refString="Cherbonnier, G. (1988) Faune de Madagascar. Publice sous les auspices du Gouvernment de la Republique Malgache, 70, O. R. S. T. O. M, Paris, 292 pp." type="book" year="1988">Cherbonnier, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[778,869,1850,1875]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">H. (?P.)</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Cherbonnier, 1988" authorityName="Cherbonnier" authorityYear="1988" box="[877,1190,1850,1876]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Holothuriidae" genus="Holothuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aspidochirotida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="insolita">
<emphasis box="[877,965,1850,1875]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">insolita</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cherbonnier, G." box="[972,1190,1850,1876]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refId="ref28924" refString="Cherbonnier, G. (1988) Faune de Madagascar. Publice sous les auspices du Gouvernment de la Republique Malgache, 70, O. R. S. T. O. M, Paris, 292 pp." type="book" year="1988">Cherbonnier, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
have been described and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ludwig, 1875" authorityName="Ludwig" authorityYear="1875" box="[202,520,1890,1916]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Holothuriidae" genus="Holothuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aspidochirotida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="samoana">
<emphasis box="[202,345,1890,1915]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">H. samoana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ludwig, H." box="[354,520,1890,1916]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="77 - 220" refId="ref29920" refString="Ludwig, H. (1875) Beitrage zur Kenntniss der Holothurien. Arbeite aus dem zoologie zootom. Institut in Wurzburg, 2, 77 - 220." type="journal article" year="1875">Ludwig, 1875</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
referred to this subgenus by Rowe (in 
<bibRefCitation author="Rowe, F. W. E. &amp; Gates, J." box="[989,1237,1890,1916]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refId="ref30851" refString="Rowe, F. W. E. &amp; Gates, J. (1995) Echinodermata. In: Wells, A. (ed), Zoological catalogue of Australia, Vol. 33, Melbourne, CSIRO Australia, xiii - 510 pp." type="book" year="1995">Rowe &amp; Gates 1995</bibRefCitation>
). Perhaps not all species are valid and must await a critical re-examination. Since 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Semper. SAM" authorityYear="1868" box="[920,1053,1930,1955]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Holothuriidae" genus="Holothuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aspidochirotida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="difficilis">
<emphasis box="[920,1053,1930,1955]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">H. difficilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is so widely distributed, several variations, probably at subspecific level, must be expected between such geographically isolated populations as those of the East Pacific, West Pacific and West Indian Oceans. This is perhaps the chief reason for the application of so many names to a species which is otherwise well characterised. 
<bibRefCitation author="Deichmann, E." box="[1101,1322,152,178]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="239 - 349" refId="ref29374" refString="Deichmann, E. (1958) The Holothuroidea collected by the ' Velero III' and ' IV' during the years 1932 - 1954, part II, Aspidochirota. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 11 (2), 239 - 349, pls 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="1958">Deichmann (1958)</bibRefCitation>
relegated many names to the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Semper. SAM" authorityYear="1868" box="[536,667,192,217]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Holothuriidae" genus="Holothuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aspidochirotida" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="difficilis">
<emphasis box="[536,667,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">H. difficilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and this is partially supported by Rowe (in 
<bibRefCitation author="Rowe, F. W. E. &amp; Gates, J." box="[1175,1423,192,218]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref30851" refString="Rowe, F. W. E. &amp; Gates, J. (1995) Echinodermata. In: Wells, A. (ed), Zoological catalogue of Australia, Vol. 33, Melbourne, CSIRO Australia, xiii - 510 pp." type="book" year="1995">Rowe &amp; Gates, 1995</bibRefCitation>
). However, some of the names may have to be reinstated, as our knowledge of the intraspecific variations within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Semper. SAM" authorityYear="1868" box="[234,366,272,297]" class="Holothuroidea" family="Holothuriidae" genus="Holothuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aspidochirotida" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="difficilis">
<emphasis box="[234,366,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">H. difficilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
increases. Colouration, presence or absence of warts and Cuvierian tubules, the maximum size at maturity, the relative dimensions of spicules and the 
<typeStatus box="[843,893,312,338]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">type</typeStatus>
of podial deposits may offer satisfactory characters. H.L. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark H. L." box="[298,472,352,378]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="221 - 435" refId="ref29162" refString="Clark H. L. (1923) The echinoderm fauna of South Africa. Annals of the South African Museum, 13, 221 - 435." type="journal article" year="1923">Clark’s (1923)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kalk, M." box="[486,649,352,378]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref29728" refString="Kalk, M. (1959) A general ecological survey of some shores in northern Mozambique. Revista de Biologia, Lisbon, 2, 1 - 24, pls. 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1959">Kalk’s (1959)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Thandar, A. S. &amp; Samyn, Y." box="[709,1035,352,378]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="253 - 260" refId="ref31338" refString="Thandar, A. S. &amp; Samyn, Y. (2004) Shallow-water holothuroid (Echinodermata: Holothuroidea) biodiversity and biogeography of the subtropical east coast of South Africa. Echinoderms: Munchen - Heinzeller &amp; Nebelsick (eds.), Taylor &amp; Francis Group, London, 2004, 253 - 260." type="journal article" year="2004">Thandar &amp; Samyn’s (2004)</bibRefCitation>
are the only published records of this species from southern Africa but the latter two include no taxonomic data while that of H.L. Clark (a record overlooked by 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, A. M. &amp; Rowe, F. W. E." box="[423,682,432,458]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref29046" refString="Clark, A. M. &amp; Rowe, F. W. E. (1971) Monograph of shallow-water Indo-West Pacific echinoderms. British Museum (Natural History), London, 238 pp." type="book" year="1971">Clark &amp; Rowe, 1971</bibRefCitation>
) was based on specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1063,1221,432,458]" name="Mozambique" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
